features: 【Ergonomic Design】Misolant ergonomic office chair is designed based on human body structure to meet various sitting posture requirements and provide a whole new sitting experience. With 2D headrest, 2D lumbar support, new linkage armrests, newly designed footrest, and ergonomic seat cushion, all these features convey the importance modern people attach to health concepts. Misolant is born for this purpose.

【2D Ergonomic Lumbar Support】Made from soft and breathable fabric, the backrest reduces discomfort caused by heat and sweat. The newly defined 2D lumbar support offers both up and down, before and after adjustments, giving you a more fulfilling support experience. Unlike single-direction up and down adjustments, the added flexibility of before and after adjustments provides you with more options. Furthermore, we include a complimentary headrest to save you from any additional expenses.

【Lock in Any Angle】The chair back is ingeniously designed to recline and lock at any angle within 155°, offering you the flexibility to adjust your relaxation mode during lunch breaks or while working. With its soft and comfortable footrest, the chair provides a cozy experience, allowing you to unwind and change your posture as needed. Moreover, the dual-function headrest can be adjusted both vertically and flipped, providing comprehensive and customizable support for your head.

【Sturdy & Installation】:Our office desk chair has passed the BIFMA testing, and has also been certified by SGS, ensuring its safety and durability for worry-free use. Each office chair comes with a detailed instruction manual, allowing you to easily understand the product's installation and usage. Installation typically takes around 25 minutes. With a small investment of time, you can have a protective office chair that keeps you comfortable and productive throughout the workday.

【One-To-One Service】：We only offer brand new products, so you don't have to worry about buying used products. Our Ergonomic desk chair comes with a one-year quality guarantee. At Misolant, we have a dedicated customer service team ready to assist you with any questions or needs, including replacement parts. Whether it is before or after sale, we warmly and sincerely welcome you. Rest assured that we're always here to help, so you can purchase our product worry-free.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A comfy and stylish chair for my home office
reviews.reviewText: I purchased a much more expensive chair during the height of the pandemic so that I could have a comfortable desk chair that also fit in with my decor - and I hated it. Since then I've been on a quest to replace that chair with something affordable, comfortable, and stylish. This chair checks all of the boxes! It was easy to assemble, and all of the position combinations with the footrest (for sitting criss cross applesauce!!!), headrest, tilt, lift, AND lumbar support make it the perfect work chair.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars really happy with it! good for dog owners who work with pups in their lap.
reviews.reviewText: i was a little skeptical at first but decided to give this chair a try after seeing something similar to it in a tiktok video of a WFH setup. i needed a new computer chair and my previous one was good and all but not as ergonomic as i would’ve liked. i’ve been using this chair for a month and a half and so far so good. my favorite part about this chair is how wide the seat is, because my pup likes to lay and sleep in my lap while i’m working. with my previous chair, it was kind of hard to have her in my lap and awkward… with this chair, it’s a lot more comfortable for the both of us. :Pi like how this chair also comes with a mini pillow and a headrest. i never owned a chair with a separate headrest and i was afraid this would get in the way but it’s very comfortable and i can adjust it to my liking if i don’t want to deal with it. same with reclining it back and lowering/raising it - it’s really easy to do. the footrest is a plus, but i don’t use it all the time. i like how you can adjust it forward or back as much as you’d like. i really only use it if my lap gets tired from my pup… loloverall 10/10 and i would definitely recommend this to anyone who’s looking for a comfortable and aesthetic-looking WFH office chair!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality and easy assembly!
reviews.reviewText: Wow! I am so impressed by the quality of this chair! I can't speak for longevity since I've only had it for a week, but very heavy duty and comfortable! I can confirm this is a chair for the bigger people out there! The highest height setting puts my feet in the air sitting all the way back and I'm a plus sized 5'8 woman. The white color makes the chair look sophisticated rather than the gaming chair look. It took me only 20 mins to assemble by myself, very straightforward instructions. I've tried 4 or 5 Amazon desk chairs throughout the years and this is BY FAR the best one I've tried in every category. Only downside to the white is I can tell sitting on it with dark denim or other dark clothing may rub off or stain the white chair fabric. It even mentions this on the paperwork that comes inside of the box. But part of this chair purchase was upgrading the esthetic of my old chair so I'll take the beautiful white any day!

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great so far!
reviews.reviewText: I’ve had this chair a few weeks now and so far I love it! Easy to put together. Comfortable. Makes sitting at my desk a lot easier!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Comfortable with Variable positioning
reviews.reviewText: I love the functionality of this chair. When I'm working on my PC, it allows me to sit straight at the level I need to be comfortable. (I'm 5'7" for reference) When I turn to watch TV I can recline back a little and fold out the foot rest to be in a more comfortable lounging position. The footrest also works as a convenient tray like surface for misc tasks or holding your dinner plate :D like I do sometimes.The chair itself is soft in cushioning but also firm enough to provide the back/hip support that many chairs do not offer. I sometimes sit for long periods of time and it provides maximum comfort during these periods. I no longer have to use additional back supports or cushions to add needed support.The chair arrived quickly after I ordered it, was very well packaged and completely free of any damage. It was also easy to assemble and I was able to do so fairly quickly on my own in minimal time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great chair, but not sure how long it will last
reviews.reviewText: So this chair is great. It took about 45 minutes to assemble. I had no issues with assembly other than the "decorative" piece on the back that covers the hardware doesnt snap in all the way. Not really a big deal. Its not a plush comfy chair, but it is spacious and I love the reclining aspect with the foot rest. It makes it so much easier for me to sit comfortably at the office. For that I give it 5 stars.The only con is it doesn't seem very durable. It seems kinda cheaply made. I'm slightly concerned about how long it will hold up, but for now it's great. Will update in a few months.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This chair has so many possible settings! I haven't had back problems since I started using it. Very easy to assemble. I did it myself within half an hour, and that was taking my time. Love the color too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars OK Chair With Some Major Flaws
reviews.reviewText: Pros:- Mesh feels nice and seems to be holding up for now.Cons:- Does not recline as much as the advertised 155° or as shown in the product video.It only reclines to around 135°- The seat cushion, while soft, does not provide enough resistance.After sitting on it for a while you'd start to feel the wood underneath.This becomes quite unbearable and pretty much forces you to get another cushion.- Sometimes when I sit on the chair it would lower for no reason, as if the pressure inside the piston is lost.This doesn't happen that often but raises some concerns about the long term longevity of the piston.
